8 POLICY COMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
9 An Act relating to schools; prohibiting private
schools from requiring a parent or guardian to
10 participate in the Oklahoma Parental Choice Tax
Credit; providing for codification; providing an
11 effective date; and declaring an emergency.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 28-104 of Title 70, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 Private schools accredited by the State Board of Education or
19 another accrediting association shall not, as a condition of
20 acceptance, enrollment, or student eligibility, require that a
21 student's parent or guardian participate in the Oklahoma Parental
22 Choice Tax Credit Program created in Section 28-101 of Title 70 of
23 the Oklahoma Statutes.
24 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
